3
00:03:59.005 --> 00:04:00.803
You don't need his approval.

4
00:04:00.907 --> 00:04:01.907
You just want it.

5
00:04:01.942 --> 00:04:03.740
What's the difference?

6
00:04:03.844 --> 00:04:07.838
Well. most of what we
call needs are desires.

7
00:04:07.948 --> 00:04:12.784
We need air to breath.
water. warmth. food to eat.

8
00:04:12.886 --> 00:04:14.582
And speaking of which...

9
00:04:14.688 --> 00:04:16.714
But the rest... love. approval.

10
00:04:16.823 --> 00:04:18.917
recognition. praise. whatever...

11
00:04:19.025 --> 00:04:20.323
They're desires.

12
00:04:20.427 --> 00:04:21.918
So. what's sex?

13
00:04:22.028 --> 00:04:24.293
Is that a need or a desire?

14
00:04:24.397 --> 00:04:25.592
Hmm.

15
00:04:25.699 --> 00:04:28.669
Well. both if
you're doing it right.

16
00:04:54.728 --> 00:04:56.356
But don't you want children?

17
00:04:56.463 --> 00:04:57.463
Of course I do.

18
00:04:57.497 --> 00:04:59.864
So. then. you do want
marriage in the end?

19
00:04:59.966 --> 00:05:02.026
I didn't know you
were so conventional.

20
00:05:04.504 --> 00:05:06.496
There's a province
somewhere in China

21
00:05:06.606 --> 00:05:07.904
where the Mosuo people live.

22
00:05:08.008 --> 00:05:10.842
The head of the family is
a mother or grandmother.

23
00:05:10.944 --> 00:05:13.345
and she controls
the family's finances.

24
00:05:13.446 --> 00:05:14.641
Marriage doesn't exist.

25
00:05:14.748 --> 00:05:16.876
Instead they practice
"walking marriage."

26
00:05:16.983 --> 00:05:19.612
A woman can invite
a man into her hut

27
00:05:19.719 --> 00:05:21.415
to spend a "sweet night."

28
00:05:21.521 --> 00:05:23.820
but he has to be
gone by daybreak.

29
00:05:23.924 --> 00:05:26.325
I'm up for that.

30
00:05:26.426 --> 00:05:29.487
The Mosuo language has no
words for war. murder. or rape.

31
00:05:29.596 --> 00:05:31.997
and there are no jails.

32
00:05:32.098 --> 00:05:33.396
Think about it.

33
00:05:33.500 --> 00:05:35.594
I'd be out of a job.

34
00:05:35.702 --> 00:05:37.034
Hmm. as would I.

35
00:05:37.337 --> 00:05:38.999
I have to take this.

36
00:05:53.753 --> 00:05:56.951
We don't want this to turn into
an international custody battle.

37
00:05:57.057 --> 00:05:57.922
We have to consider

38
00:05:58.024 --> 00:05:59.993
the emotional well-being
of your children.

39
00:06:00.093 --> 00:06:02.528
They're in France. and
I want them back ASAP.

40
00:06:02.629 --> 00:06:03.989
- This is not acceptable.
- Look...

41
00:06:04.064 --> 00:06:05.828
What the hell am
I paying you for?

42
00:06:05.932 --> 00:06:07.560
I will go into the
office tomorrow.

43
00:06:07.667 --> 00:06:09.045
Look. we need to
get this sorted now.

44
00:06:09.069 --> 00:06:10.503
We can talk it through then.

45
00:06:10.604 --> 00:06:12.095
I will ring you first thing.

46
00:06:12.405 --> 00:06:15.432
- You better.
- Okay. Bye.

47
00:06:19.813 --> 00:06:21.782
I should go.

48
00:06:21.882 --> 00:06:23.748
It's Friday night.

49
00:06:23.850 --> 00:06:26.376
Seems I have work to do.

50
00:06:51.411 --> 00:06:52.538
What are you doing?

51
00:06:52.646 --> 00:06:54.046
I've just got you a drink.

52
00:06:54.147 --> 00:06:56.116
I've had two already.
That's my limit.

53
00:06:56.416 --> 00:06:57.509
Three and I'm anyone's.

54
00:06:57.617 --> 00:06:58.482
That's the plan.

55
00:06:58.585 --> 00:07:01.749
Oh. I know. That's
why I'm going home.

56
00:08:40.954 --> 00:08:42.718
I'm calling the police.

57
00:08:42.822 --> 00:08:45.621
If you're still here.
you should go.

58
00:08:45.725 --> 00:08:47.557
I'm calling the police!

59
00:09:00.740 --> 00:09:02.606
Police officers!

60
00:09:04.044 --> 00:09:06.980
We're entering
with weapons drawn.

61
00:09:07.080 --> 00:09:11.745
If anyone is in the house. make
your presence known immediately.

62
00:09:20.860 --> 00:09:22.294
Alpha Papa 1-0 to Uniform.

63
00:09:22.595 --> 00:09:25.895
Checking the rear area now.

64
00:10:02.602 --> 00:10:04.901
Police officer.

65
00:10:05.004 --> 00:10:08.600
It's okay. There's no one here.

66
00:10:08.708 --> 00:10:10.768
Okay.

67
00:10:32.165 --> 00:10:34.191
Daddy?

68
00:10:34.300 --> 00:10:37.099
Where have you been?

69
00:10:42.408 --> 00:10:44.001
What are you doing out of bed?

70
00:10:44.110 --> 00:10:45.601
I was frightened.

71
00:10:45.712 --> 00:10:47.908
I woke up. and you weren't here.

72
00:10:48.014 --> 00:10:50.347
I just popped out. Just
to the all-night shop.

73
00:10:50.650 --> 00:10:51.879
Why?

74
00:10:51.985 --> 00:10:53.715
To get some headache pills.

75
00:10:53.820 --> 00:10:55.618
We have headache pills.

76
00:10:55.722 --> 00:10:58.624
Mummy keeps them
up in the bathroom.

77
00:10:58.725 --> 00:11:00.057
I've just been five minutes.

78
00:11:00.160 --> 00:11:02.288
No. you haven't.
You've been ages.

79
00:11:02.395 --> 00:11:03.761
I called your phone.

80
00:11:03.863 --> 00:11:06.890
I didn't take it with me.

81
00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:09.970
Come here.

82
00:11:16.776 --> 00:11:19.211
What's in your bag?

83
00:11:19.312 --> 00:11:21.645
Just some stuff from the shop.

84
00:11:21.748 --> 00:11:25.879
I tried to ring Mummy.
but I got her number wrong.

85
00:11:28.922 --> 00:11:29.821
I'm sorry.

86
00:11:29.923 --> 00:11:33.416
I promise I won't go and
leave you again. okay?

87
00:11:33.726 --> 00:11:36.958
Cross my heart and hope
to die. Only don't tell Mummy.

88
00:11:37.063 --> 00:11:38.793
She'll be cross.

89
00:11:38.898 --> 00:11:39.898
With me?

90
00:11:39.999 --> 00:11:42.935
No. no. with me.

91
00:11:45.271 --> 00:11:47.900
Kiss Mac.

92
00:11:56.749 --> 00:11:58.081
Is this your underwear?

93
00:11:58.184 --> 00:11:59.208
Yes.

94
00:12:03.256 --> 00:12:05.020
Oh. my God!

95
00:12:05.124 --> 00:12:08.094
Is that yours. too?

96
00:12:08.194 --> 00:12:09.992
Yes.

97
00:12:11.164 --> 00:12:14.396
And you didn't just leave
these things on the bed yourself?

98
00:12:14.500 --> 00:12:17.868
No. I...

99
00:12:17.971 --> 00:12:20.839
No.

100
00:12:20.940 --> 00:12:23.000
Where have you been
this evening. Sarah?

101
00:12:23.109 --> 00:12:26.705
Out with some colleagues
in the city center.

102
00:12:26.813 --> 00:12:28.324
And what do you do for a living?

103
00:12:28.348 --> 00:12:29.213
I'm a solicitor.

104
00:12:29.315 --> 00:12:30.874
And you've been drinking?

105
00:12:30.984 --> 00:12:33.078
Just some wine.

106
00:12:33.186 --> 00:12:35.849
How much wine. Sarah?

107
00:13:28.374 --> 00:13:31.503
No sign of forced entry.

108
00:13:31.811 --> 00:13:33.473
Who else has keys to the house?

109
00:13:33.579 --> 00:13:35.514
My sister. she has keys.

110
00:13:35.815 --> 00:13:38.410
And she wouldn't have
done this? As a joke?

111
00:13:38.518 --> 00:13:39.781
What? No.

112
00:13:39.886 --> 00:13:42.355
No boyfriend who has keys?

113
00:13:42.455 --> 00:13:44.219
No.

114
00:13:44.324 --> 00:13:46.555
An ex? Could have kept keys?

115
00:13:46.859 --> 00:13:50.091
Um. I don't know.

116
00:13:50.196 --> 00:13:52.188
I see you have a cat.

117
00:13:52.298 --> 00:13:53.493
Yeah.

118
00:13:53.599 --> 00:13:56.034
The cat couldn't have. I
don't know. been on the bed?

119
00:13:58.071 --> 00:14:01.007
Have you checked the
loft? Can you check the loft?

120
00:14:05.244 --> 00:14:08.373
Is anything missing?

121
00:14:08.481 --> 00:14:11.246
Where was the underwear kept?

122
00:14:11.351 --> 00:14:15.015
The underwear is here
in these top two drawers.

123
00:14:15.121 --> 00:14:18.922
The other thing is in the
bedside cabinet drawer.

124
00:14:21.894 --> 00:14:24.261
I think...

125
00:14:24.364 --> 00:14:27.960
maybe some underwear's gone.

126
00:14:46.185 --> 00:14:47.278
Loft is clear.

127
00:14:48.654 --> 00:14:49.883
Oh.

128
00:14:52.959 --> 00:14:53.959
It's a client.

129
00:14:53.993 --> 00:14:56.360
Isn't it rather late for that?

130
00:14:56.462 --> 00:14:57.987
Yeah. it is.

131
00:14:58.097 --> 00:15:00.032
I think maybe
you should just go.

132
00:15:00.133 --> 00:15:03.069
I... I have to be up in the
morning to deal with this.

133
00:15:04.670 --> 00:15:08.334
I really appreciate you
coming. but I need to sleep.

134
00:15:10.009 --> 00:15:12.121
If you're worried. you should
stay with a family member.

135
00:15:12.145 --> 00:15:13.204
a friend.

136
00:15:13.312 --> 00:15:15.440
Yeah. yeah. I'll call my sister.

137
00:15:15.548 --> 00:15:17.210
Just make sure you
don't drive anywhere.

138
00:15:17.316 --> 00:15:18.316
I won't.

139
00:15:18.351 --> 00:15:20.149
If you're not sure who
might still have keys.

140
00:15:20.253 --> 00:15:21.516
you should change the locks.

141
00:15:21.621 --> 00:15:23.988
I will. Thank you.

142
00:15:24.090 --> 00:15:27.959
Sorry. I just want to go to bed.

143
00:15:30.163 --> 00:15:33.133
We've checked the premises
and surrounding area.

144
00:15:33.232 --> 00:15:34.393
No intruder located.

145
00:15:34.500 --> 00:15:37.595
We've given assurances
we'll pay passing attention

146
00:15:37.703 --> 00:15:39.137
throughout the night.

147
00:15:39.238 --> 00:15:41.298
What?

148
00:15:41.407 --> 00:15:43.342
Could it have been the cat?

149
00:15:43.443 --> 00:15:44.443
She's drunk.

150
00:15:44.510 --> 00:15:48.971
That's her excuse. What's yours?

151
00:16:14.674 --> 00:16:19.112
You could have
warmed my side for me.

152
00:16:19.212 --> 00:16:21.943
Why would I do that?

153
00:16:22.048 --> 00:16:25.416
You horrible man.

154
00:17:10.162 --> 00:17:12.427
Would that be Detective
Superintendent Gibson?

155
00:17:12.532 --> 00:17:16.663
- Yes. ma'am.
- Then that would be me.

156
00:17:25.278 --> 00:17:26.746
Stella.

157
00:17:27.046 --> 00:17:30.039
Nice to see you.

158
00:17:30.149 --> 00:17:32.516
Armored car. Jim?

159
00:17:32.618 --> 00:17:35.019
Welcome to Belfast.

160
00:17:38.291 --> 00:17:41.591
He's a good man.
Very experienced.

161
00:17:41.694 --> 00:17:45.461
First and foremost. we want
to progress the investigation.

162
00:17:45.565 --> 00:17:47.500
We don't want a trial by audit.

163
00:17:47.600 --> 00:17:50.195
I've done 28-day
reviews before. sir.

164
00:17:50.303 --> 00:17:51.669
Not here you haven't.

165
00:17:51.771 --> 00:17:53.330
Things are different here.

166
00:17:53.439 --> 00:17:54.439
What?

167
00:17:54.540 --> 00:17:57.476
All that my Jesus is better
than your Jesus stuff?

168
00:17:57.577 --> 00:17:59.705
Policing is political
here. Stella.

169
00:17:59.812 --> 00:18:02.043
And it isn't at the Met?

170
00:18:02.148 --> 00:18:06.108
The victim's ex-father-in-law
is a Unionist M.P.

171
00:18:06.218 --> 00:18:07.413
Morgan Monroe.

172
00:18:07.520 --> 00:18:09.421
Unionist M.P.. ex-lawyer.

173
00:18:09.522 --> 00:18:11.684
a chair of the Independent
Policing Executive.

174
00:18:11.791 --> 00:18:14.056
I haven't walked in
here totally unprepared.

175
00:18:14.160 --> 00:18:16.391
Good.

176
00:18:18.431 --> 00:18:21.299
We have nothing. Stella.

177
00:18:22.602 --> 00:18:25.367
The killer is out
there somewhere.

178
00:18:25.471 --> 00:18:27.531
and we have nothing at all.

179
00:19:36.509 --> 00:19:39.343
This is Detective
Superintendent Gibson.

180
00:19:39.445 --> 00:19:41.277
She's seen your file.

181
00:19:41.380 --> 00:19:43.576
so I'll let you make
your own introductions.

182
00:19:43.683 --> 00:19:45.549
Garrett Brink.
Pleased to meet you.

183
00:19:45.651 --> 00:19:47.586
Is there anything you need?

184
00:19:47.687 --> 00:19:48.687
Is that coffee?

185
00:19:48.788 --> 00:19:51.257
It's actually hard to tell.

186
00:19:51.357 --> 00:19:54.486
I'll risk a cup.

187
00:19:55.928 --> 00:19:58.193
I'll have your case
taken to your hotel.

188
00:19:58.297 --> 00:20:01.495
Thank you. sir.

189
00:20:12.211 --> 00:20:14.612
It's been three months.

190
00:20:14.714 --> 00:20:18.845
and I haven't even
stepped into his room.

191
00:20:21.554 --> 00:20:25.787
A can of Coke he had the
day before is still sitting there.

192
00:20:28.661 --> 00:20:31.324
You know. at first. they
thought it was a virus.

193
00:20:31.430 --> 00:20:34.923
You've told him before.

194
00:20:35.234 --> 00:20:37.965
Gave him paracetamol.

195
00:20:39.538 --> 00:20:42.531
By the time they put him
on antibiotics. it was too late.

196
00:20:42.641 --> 00:20:44.803
The boy told the
doctors he felt better.

197
00:20:44.910 --> 00:20:47.675
He'd have said anything
to be allowed to go home!

198
00:20:53.953 --> 00:20:55.387
Are you eating?

199
00:20:56.856 --> 00:20:59.451
Not really.

200
00:20:59.558 --> 00:21:01.857
How are things in the bedroom?

201
00:21:16.475 --> 00:21:19.934
Before they took him away.

202
00:21:20.045 --> 00:21:25.484
I painted his hands and his feet

203
00:21:25.584 --> 00:21:29.885
and made prints.

204
00:21:32.858 --> 00:21:35.987
Three other people are
living because of him.

205
00:21:38.030 --> 00:21:43.298
A little boy regained his
sight because of our Daniel.

206
00:21:45.571 --> 00:21:48.268
That's something.

207
00:21:51.310 --> 00:21:54.405
It's almost like
he's still living.

208
00:21:54.513 --> 00:22:00.043
Somewhere his heart is beating.

209
00:22:01.654 --> 00:22:04.351
Come in.

210
00:22:04.456 --> 00:22:07.756
Jerry McElroy.

211
00:22:07.860 --> 00:22:09.658
You asked to see me.

212
00:22:09.762 --> 00:22:11.321
Come in. Jerry.

213
00:22:11.797 --> 00:22:13.425
I'm Detective
Superintendent Gibson.

214
00:22:13.532 --> 00:22:14.556
Ma'am.

215
00:22:14.667 --> 00:22:17.728
This is DCI Brink.
who I think you know.

216
00:22:17.837 --> 00:22:19.669
Jerry and I go way back.

217
00:22:19.772 --> 00:22:21.035
Have a seat.

218
00:22:22.842 --> 00:22:25.539
I've been brought in from
the Metropolitan Police

219
00:22:25.644 --> 00:22:26.543
to lead a review

220
00:22:26.645 --> 00:22:29.479
into the investigation of
the murder of Alice Monroe.

221
00:22:29.582 --> 00:22:31.642
Yes. ma'am.

222
00:22:31.750 --> 00:22:34.481
As the senior investigating
officer on that case. Jerry.

223
00:22:34.587 --> 00:22:36.749
we want to work closely with you

224
00:22:36.856 --> 00:22:39.792
to advance the
investigation if we can.

225
00:22:39.892 --> 00:22:41.360
not to find fault.

226
00:22:41.460 --> 00:22:45.591
If any problems are
identified through review.

227
00:22:45.698 --> 00:22:47.496
you will be notified immediately

228
00:22:47.600 --> 00:22:50.434
so that remedial action
can be taken if possible.

229
00:22:50.536 --> 00:22:51.765
I see.

230
00:22:51.871 --> 00:22:55.364
I will be looking at the
investigative response...

231
00:22:55.474 --> 00:22:56.942
The initial actions
at the scene.

232
00:22:57.042 --> 00:22:59.637
information gathering. witness
and suspect management.

233
00:22:59.745 --> 00:23:01.111
together with forensic issues...

234
00:23:01.413 --> 00:23:02.938
Exhibit management
and submission.

235
00:23:03.048 --> 00:23:05.882
And I'm going to be
looking at record keeping...

236
00:23:05.985 --> 00:23:08.454
Document management.
action administration...

237
00:23:08.554 --> 00:23:09.988
Together with communications...

238
00:23:10.089 --> 00:23:12.684
Internal. external. and
with the victim's family.

239
00:23:12.791 --> 00:23:14.760
We will. in time.

240
00:23:14.860 --> 00:23:18.126
read all documentation
relating to the inquiry.

241
00:23:18.430 --> 00:23:19.693
To that end.

242
00:23:19.798 --> 00:23:24.702
I will need your policy
book and your action book.

243
00:23:24.803 --> 00:23:26.999
Yeah. I have them here.

244
00:23:27.106 --> 00:23:29.905
Any questions?

245
00:23:31.911 --> 00:23:35.507
I feel so alone.

246
00:23:41.487 --> 00:23:44.150
Have you anything to say. Jimmy?

247
00:23:44.456 --> 00:23:45.617
Of course he doesn't.

248
00:23:45.724 --> 00:23:47.716
Sitting there.

249
00:23:47.826 --> 00:23:51.593
The hard man.

250
00:23:51.697 --> 00:23:53.859
Useless waste of space.

251
00:23:57.503 --> 00:24:01.770
Men and women express
grief differently. Liz.

252
00:24:01.874 --> 00:24:05.174
Try not to make comparisons.

253
00:24:08.480 --> 00:24:12.679
How long am I going
to feel like this. Paul?

254
00:24:28.901 --> 00:24:30.494
How things are in the bedroom

255
00:24:30.602 --> 00:24:32.503
is none of your
fucking business.

256
00:24:32.604 --> 00:24:35.164
I'm sorry if you're
uncomfortable with the question.

257
00:24:35.474 --> 00:24:37.841
"Uncomfortable" doesn't
even begin to cover it.

258
00:24:37.943 --> 00:24:40.071
My wife says it comforts her

259
00:24:40.179 --> 00:24:43.980
to think of our dead
son giving life to others.

260
00:24:44.083 --> 00:24:45.984
How does it make you feel?

261
00:24:46.085 --> 00:24:47.917
How does it make me feel?

262
00:24:48.020 --> 00:24:50.785
His heart beating in
some Taig's chest?

263
00:24:50.889 --> 00:24:53.188
It makes me feel sick.

264
00:24:53.492 --> 00:24:55.586
I've done things.

265
00:24:55.694 --> 00:24:59.529
Bad things. In the past.

266
00:24:59.631 --> 00:25:00.963
Really bad things.

267
00:25:01.066 --> 00:25:05.834
And my son has paid the price.

268
00:25:05.938 --> 00:25:09.466
Your son had bacterial
meningitis. Jimmy.

269
00:25:09.575 --> 00:25:13.012
An illness. that's all.

270
00:25:16.749 --> 00:25:21.881
You don't believe a son has
to pay for the sins of his father?

271
00:25:22.721 --> 00:25:23.916
No. I don't.

272
00:25:25.157 --> 00:25:26.921
Don't you believe in God?

273
00:25:28.193 --> 00:25:29.684
Jimmy. let me go.

274
00:25:29.795 --> 00:25:32.196
Answer me.

275
00:25:33.198 --> 00:25:36.828
Of course I believe in God.

276
00:25:36.935 --> 00:25:39.495
And Jesus Christ. too.

277
00:25:39.605 --> 00:25:42.905
I have seen angels ascending
and descending Jacob's Ladder.

278
00:25:43.008 --> 00:25:46.968
Is that what you want to hear?

279
00:25:47.079 --> 00:25:49.776
It makes no odds
what I believe. Jimmy.

280
00:25:49.882 --> 00:25:52.283
It's what you
believe that matters.

281
00:25:53.786 --> 00:25:57.120
Now let me go.

282
00:26:01.593 --> 00:26:04.757
What kind of name
is Spector. anyway?

283
00:26:04.863 --> 00:26:06.024
It's Russian.

284
00:26:06.131 --> 00:26:08.600
Jewish.

285
00:26:08.700 --> 00:26:11.829
That explains a lot.

286
00:27:52.905 --> 00:27:55.340
Daddy. look what I found!

287
00:27:55.440 --> 00:27:56.703
Where did you get that?

288
00:27:56.808 --> 00:27:58.401
You're not supposed
to pick things.

289
00:27:58.710 --> 00:28:00.906
It was on the floor.

290
00:28:01.013 --> 00:28:02.777
I'm not lying.

291
00:28:02.881 --> 00:28:06.318
Give it to me.

292
00:28:06.418 --> 00:28:09.650
Come on.

293
00:28:13.859 --> 00:28:15.384
Hey.

294
00:28:15.694 --> 00:28:16.957
Hey. You all right?

295
00:28:17.062 --> 00:28:20.157
Shall we sit?

296
00:28:25.304 --> 00:28:28.365
How much do I grow every night?

297
00:28:28.473 --> 00:28:30.999
I don't know. A
little bit probably.

298
00:28:31.109 --> 00:28:32.702
But you know you only grow

299
00:28:32.811 --> 00:28:35.280
if you go to sleep
straightaway at bedtime

300
00:28:35.380 --> 00:28:37.042
and you stay
asleep all night long.

301
00:28:37.149 --> 00:28:38.811
You should have called me.

302
00:28:38.917 --> 00:28:41.409
I didn't want to wake you.
I didn't want to wake Lucy.

303
00:28:41.720 --> 00:28:43.450
I'm your sister
for Christ's sake.

304
00:28:43.755 --> 00:28:45.053
You should have come over.

305
00:28:45.157 --> 00:28:46.056
I was tired.

306
00:28:46.158 --> 00:28:48.718
I'd had a couple
of glasses of wine.

307
00:28:48.827 --> 00:28:50.386
Even so.

308
00:28:52.197 --> 00:28:55.258
I've been thinking. who
might still have keys?

309
00:28:55.367 --> 00:28:57.962
Nobody now. I got
the locks changed.

310
00:28:58.070 --> 00:28:59.698
The front anyway.

311
00:28:59.805 --> 00:29:03.367
The back door needs
replaced. apparently.

312
00:29:04.910 --> 00:29:06.845
I'm glad I'm 8.

313
00:29:06.945 --> 00:29:10.177
It's the oldest I've
been in my entire life.

314
00:29:10.282 --> 00:29:12.877
Why don't you stay with us.

315
00:29:12.985 --> 00:29:14.851
at least until the
back door's done.

316
00:29:14.953 --> 00:29:17.115
I can't. I have too
much work to do.

317
00:29:17.222 --> 00:29:20.283
Shall we go? Come on.

318
00:29:21.927 --> 00:29:23.828
Oh. gosh. you're heavy.

319
00:29:23.929 --> 00:29:27.798
Tell me about the
three billy goats.

320
00:29:27.899 --> 00:29:29.492
Once upon a time...

321
00:29:29.801 --> 00:29:32.168
Oh. it's the best smell
in the whole world.

322
00:29:32.271 --> 00:29:35.366
There's no evidence of
any defensive wounds.

323
00:29:35.474 --> 00:29:40.503
Maybe she was too fearful

324
00:29:40.812 --> 00:29:43.077
or thought co-operation
would make things better

325
00:29:43.181 --> 00:29:44.843
or he overpowered her

326
00:29:44.950 --> 00:29:48.148
so she didn't have a
chance to fight back.

327
00:29:48.253 --> 00:29:52.384
But whatever. he had things
entirely under his control.

328
00:29:53.425 --> 00:29:57.760
Which leads me to think that
this was not his first murder.

329
00:29:57.863 --> 00:30:02.961
Now. the pathologist reports
extensive petechial hemorrhages

330
00:30:03.068 --> 00:30:08.871
that suggest that the killer
tightened and loosened his grip

331
00:30:08.974 --> 00:30:10.806
around her throat

332
00:30:10.909 --> 00:30:14.937
over a period of 45
minutes to an hour.

333
00:30:17.382 --> 00:30:18.975
I was part of a review team.

334
00:30:19.084 --> 00:30:21.246
Now. this was
actually a 7-day review.

335
00:30:21.353 --> 00:30:24.152
and I remember the
pathologist on that case making

336
00:30:24.256 --> 00:30:25.383
the same observation.

337
00:30:25.490 --> 00:30:26.549
When was this?

338
00:30:26.858 --> 00:30:28.087
Three months ago.

339
00:30:28.193 --> 00:30:31.186
It was felt at the time.
still is. as far as I know.

340
00:30:31.296 --> 00:30:33.822
that the killer was
known to the victim.

341
00:30:33.932 --> 00:30:37.835
She had. at the time of her
death. more than one boyfriend.

342
00:30:37.936 --> 00:30:40.371
Boyfriend one was
quickly eliminated.

343
00:30:40.472 --> 00:30:43.931
Boyfriend two left the
country. fled. disappeared.

344
00:30:44.042 --> 00:30:47.012
He remains the prime
suspect. I believe.

345
00:30:47.112 --> 00:30:48.122
A white professional woman?

346
00:30:48.146 --> 00:30:50.115
A teacher at the university.

347
00:30:50.215 --> 00:30:52.810
In her early 30s?

348
00:30:57.522 --> 00:31:00.048
Posed after death?

349
00:31:00.158 --> 00:31:06.530
Only if you call being stuffed
in the bedroom closet posed.

350
00:31:14.072 --> 00:31:16.041
What was her name?

351
00:31:16.141 --> 00:31:19.009
Fiona Gallagher.

352
00:31:24.316 --> 00:31:28.185
The essence to a committed
relationship is exclusivity.

353
00:31:28.286 --> 00:31:29.982
Physical and emotional.

354
00:31:30.088 --> 00:31:33.320
Anything that impinges on
that is cheating and harmful.

355
00:31:33.425 --> 00:31:36.452
Jesus. you should have
your own daytime TV show.

356
00:31:36.561 --> 00:31:39.030
I mean. what is it. £20 a dance?

357
00:31:39.131 --> 00:31:41.396
That's money you could
have spent on your kids

358
00:31:41.500 --> 00:31:42.263
or on me even!

359
00:31:42.367 --> 00:31:45.235
Well. maybe you shouldn't
go through my pockets.

360
00:31:45.337 --> 00:31:46.999
Seven years of marriage.

361
00:31:47.105 --> 00:31:49.006
Seven years of
marriage and now this.

362
00:31:49.107 --> 00:31:51.372
Jesus. Nothing
happens in those places.

363
00:31:51.476 --> 00:31:53.206
It's just flirting.

364
00:31:53.311 --> 00:31:54.311
Oh?

365
00:31:54.346 --> 00:31:55.370
That's the name you give

366
00:31:55.480 --> 00:31:58.006
to somebody pushing their
silicone tits in your face?

367
00:31:58.116 --> 00:31:59.175
It is! It's flirting!

368
00:31:59.284 --> 00:32:01.362
The promise of something
that will never. ever happen.

369
00:32:01.386 --> 00:32:02.386
Yeah. only because

370
00:32:02.454 --> 00:32:03.979
no laptop dancer
would ever have you.

371
00:32:04.089 --> 00:32:05.990
Lap dancer.

372
00:32:06.091 --> 00:32:07.286
What?

373
00:32:07.392 --> 00:32:09.657
Not laptop.

374
00:32:09.961 --> 00:32:11.122
Lap dancer.

375
00:32:11.229 --> 00:32:13.130
Looking isn't cheating.

376
00:32:13.231 --> 00:32:14.631
It's just fantasy.

377
00:32:14.933 --> 00:32:16.277
It's your own fault
for getting caught.

378
00:32:16.301 --> 00:32:17.894
You should have
destroyed the evidence.

379
00:32:18.003 --> 00:32:19.938
Not helpful.

380
00:32:20.038 --> 00:32:21.973
Same again?

381
00:33:19.297 --> 00:33:21.095
Excuse me?

382
00:33:21.199 --> 00:33:23.031
Is this your purse?

383
00:33:24.336 --> 00:33:25.668
Yeah. it is.

384
00:33:25.770 --> 00:33:27.136
It was on the floor.

385
00:33:27.239 --> 00:33:30.368
Oh. thank you so much.

386
00:33:57.602 --> 00:33:59.332
Hi.

387
00:33:59.437 --> 00:34:00.437
How were they?

388
00:34:00.505 --> 00:34:02.303
Fine.

389
00:34:02.407 --> 00:34:03.534
Did you have a nice evening?

390
00:34:03.642 --> 00:34:06.339
Very nice.

391
00:34:07.212 --> 00:34:09.010
Four hours?

392
00:34:09.114 --> 00:34:10.673
Thank you.

393
00:34:23.228 --> 00:34:25.493
Paul will walk you home.

394
00:34:36.241 --> 00:34:39.234
English. I like.

395
00:34:39.344 --> 00:34:41.643
Art.

396
00:34:41.746 --> 00:34:44.807
I love music.

397
00:34:45.116 --> 00:34:47.278
I'm a singer.

398
00:34:47.385 --> 00:34:49.752
What sort of singer?

399
00:34:49.854 --> 00:34:52.414
I posted a couple
of clips online.

400
00:34:52.524 --> 00:34:54.220
Really?

401
00:34:54.326 --> 00:34:56.261
You should take a look.

402
00:34:56.361 --> 00:34:57.761
Maybe I will.

403
00:34:57.862 --> 00:35:00.263
Where can I find you?

404
00:35:00.365 --> 00:35:04.132
Oh. no. I'm not
telling you that.

405
00:35:04.235 --> 00:35:05.567
If you want to see them.

406
00:35:05.670 --> 00:35:08.071
you're going to
have to work at it.

407
00:35:08.173 --> 00:35:11.166
Track me down.

408
00:35:11.276 --> 00:35:13.438
I'm worth it.

409
00:35:17.616 --> 00:35:19.141
You look different.

410
00:35:19.250 --> 00:35:21.242
From when you last baby-sat.

411
00:35:21.353 --> 00:35:23.151
That was months ago.

412
00:35:23.254 --> 00:35:25.189
Yes.

413
00:35:25.290 --> 00:35:28.749
I've had my braces removed.

414
00:35:31.896 --> 00:35:35.128
Thank you for walking me home.

415
00:37:32.283 --> 00:37:34.616
What's the matter with you?

416
00:37:34.719 --> 00:37:38.383
Hmm? You been fighting?

417
00:37:56.341 --> 00:37:57.434
It's okay. Olivia.

418
00:37:57.542 --> 00:37:59.738
It's okay. darling.
Mummy's coming.

419
00:37:59.844 --> 00:38:00.937
Mummy!

420
00:38:12.957 --> 00:38:15.358
Shh. It's okay.

421
00:38:15.460 --> 00:38:16.655
It's all right.

422
00:38:16.761 --> 00:38:18.593
Just another bad dream.

423
00:38:18.696 --> 00:38:20.562
It's okay.

424
00:38:20.665 --> 00:38:21.997
It's okay.

425
00:38:22.300 --> 00:38:24.360
Shh.

426
00:38:26.371 --> 00:38:28.567
Shh.

427
00:38:29.874 --> 00:38:30.874
Mummy?

428
00:38:30.909 --> 00:38:32.844
It's okay. Mummy's here.

429
00:38:32.944 --> 00:38:34.503
It's all right. Come here.

430
00:38:34.612 --> 00:38:35.612
It's all right.

431
00:38:35.647 --> 00:38:38.583
It's just a bad dream.
It's okay. Shh. shh. shh.

432
00:38:38.683 --> 00:38:40.652
- Mummy.
- It's okay. Shh.

433
00:38:40.752 --> 00:38:44.018
It's all right. Mummy's here.

434
00:38:44.322 --> 00:38:46.621
Shh.

435
00:38:46.724 --> 00:38:49.558
It's okay.

436
00:38:49.661 --> 00:38:50.754
It's all right.

437
00:38:50.862 --> 00:38:53.798
Shh. shh. shh. shh.

438
00:39:38.476 --> 00:39:41.969
Shh.

439
00:39:45.483 --> 00:39:48.510
How is she?

440
00:39:51.389 --> 00:39:53.949
Shh.

441
00:41:49.707 --> 00:41:52.040
Hey. are you asleep?

442
00:41:52.143 --> 00:41:54.169
No.

443
00:41:54.278 --> 00:41:57.248
How is she?

444
00:41:57.548 --> 00:41:59.676
Did you tell her that
she wouldn't grow

445
00:41:59.784 --> 00:42:01.912
if she didn't sleep
all night through?

446
00:42:03.121 --> 00:42:05.818
You need to be careful
what you say to her.

447
00:42:07.859 --> 00:42:09.919
She's been having
night terrors for months.

448
00:42:10.028 --> 00:42:11.997
What I said has
nothing to do with it.

449
00:42:13.164 --> 00:42:15.497
She doesn't like being teased.

450
00:42:15.600 --> 00:42:18.968
Especially not by her daddy.

451
00:42:29.614 --> 00:42:33.984
I just wish I knew what
was going on in her mind

452
00:42:34.085 --> 00:42:36.054
when she's like that.

453
00:42:36.154 --> 00:42:40.854
No one knows what's going
on in someone else's mind.

454
00:42:40.958 --> 00:42:45.623
And life would be
intolerable if we did.

455
00:43:41.319 --> 00:43:43.754
I hope I'm not keeping
you from church.

456
00:43:43.855 --> 00:43:45.915
Already been.

457
00:44:03.241 --> 00:44:07.144
I brought you in to progress
the Monroe investigation.

458
00:44:07.245 --> 00:44:10.977
You need a new and
substantial line of inquiry.

459
00:44:11.082 --> 00:44:13.642
and linking these two
murders would give you one.

460
00:44:14.685 --> 00:44:18.053
We already have a prime
suspect in the Gallagher case.

461
00:44:18.156 --> 00:44:19.215
Patrick Warwick.

462
00:44:19.323 --> 00:44:22.088
His brother provided DNA
which is a familial match

463
00:44:22.193 --> 00:44:24.321
to the DNA gathered
at the crime scene.

464
00:44:24.428 --> 00:44:26.863
That doesn't mean it
was the killer's DNA.

465
00:44:26.964 --> 00:44:28.796
She was in a
relationship with Warwick.

466
00:44:28.900 --> 00:44:29.993
So there's no real surprise

467
00:44:30.101 --> 00:44:31.865
that his sperm was
found in her esophagus.

468
00:44:31.969 --> 00:44:33.995
If he didn't kill her.
then why has he fled?

469
00:44:34.105 --> 00:44:35.198
I don't know.

470
00:44:35.306 --> 00:44:37.104
There was no
sign of forced entry.

471
00:44:37.208 --> 00:44:40.076
so it was assumed that she
knew the killer and let him in.

472
00:44:40.178 --> 00:44:42.079
But I think that
assumption is false.

473
00:44:42.180 --> 00:44:44.081
It was treated as a
self-solver from the off.

474
00:44:44.182 --> 00:44:45.182
and I think that's wrong.

475
00:44:45.283 --> 00:44:49.015
Alice Monroe was
found posed in her bed.

476
00:44:49.120 --> 00:44:51.089
Gallagher stuffed
into a cupboard.

477
00:44:51.189 --> 00:44:53.920
The postmortem interval
puts the time of death

478
00:44:54.025 --> 00:44:55.926
at an hour before
she was discovered.

479
00:44:56.027 --> 00:44:57.027
She called her boyfriend

480
00:44:57.061 --> 00:44:58.927
and told him she was
going out with friends.

481
00:44:59.030 --> 00:45:02.023
He came home after
work at 1:30 in the morning.

482
00:45:02.133 --> 00:45:04.762
assumed that she was
still out. and called her.

483
00:45:04.869 --> 00:45:07.805
Her phone rang in the closet.

484
00:45:07.905 --> 00:45:10.340
He went to look and found
her stuffed inside. dead.

485
00:45:10.441 --> 00:45:13.309
Now. one possibility is that
the killer was still with her

486
00:45:13.411 --> 00:45:15.778
when the boyfriend came
home and disturbed him.

487
00:45:15.880 --> 00:45:17.940
So he shoved her in
the cupboard and fled.

488
00:45:19.817 --> 00:45:21.877
I just don't buy it.

489
00:45:21.986 --> 00:45:25.354
This would account for the
three months between this murder

490
00:45:25.456 --> 00:45:27.322
and the killing of Alice Monroe.

491
00:45:27.425 --> 00:45:30.827
It didn't go as
planned with Gallagher.

492
00:45:30.928 --> 00:45:32.396
and it spooked him.

493
00:45:32.496 --> 00:45:35.398
And so when he struck again.
he made sure that he did it right.

494
00:45:40.238 --> 00:45:43.800
Two professional
women in their early 30s

495
00:45:43.908 --> 00:45:47.367
killed in their own
homes by strangulation.

496
00:45:47.478 --> 00:45:49.242
I mean. look. they
could be sisters.

497
00:45:53.884 --> 00:45:56.046
The strangulation
marks are different.

498
00:45:56.153 --> 00:45:57.951
Yes. the marks
might be different.

499
00:45:58.055 --> 00:46:00.718
but both of them have
extensive petechial hemorrhages.

500
00:46:00.825 --> 00:46:02.794
which indicates that
he strangled them.

501
00:46:02.893 --> 00:46:04.259
released. and then
strangled again.

502
00:46:04.362 --> 00:46:05.159
over and over.

503
00:46:05.263 --> 00:46:07.289
So now you're adding
torture into the mix?

504
00:46:07.398 --> 00:46:08.798
Well. it might be sadism

505
00:46:08.899 --> 00:46:11.300
or it might just be that
his hand lacks strength.

506
00:46:11.402 --> 00:46:12.893
I mean. you try it.

507
00:46:13.004 --> 00:46:15.496
Go on. grab my wrist. See
how long you can grip it.

508
00:46:20.811 --> 00:46:23.474
No. thank you.

509
00:46:23.781 --> 00:46:27.912
It's amazing how
quickly your hand tires.

510
00:46:40.965 --> 00:46:43.958
Stop for God's sake.

511
00:46:48.339 --> 00:46:51.275
I mean. how long
was that? 30 seconds?

512
00:46:53.878 --> 00:46:56.404
Go back to your review. Stella.

513
00:46:56.514 --> 00:47:00.918
I don't want the
two murders linked.

514
00:47:27.845 --> 00:47:33.876
♪ Rain clouds are moving
across an empty sky ♪

515
00:47:33.984 --> 00:47:39.890
♪ Leaving their shadow
on my sleepless eye ♪

516
00:47:39.990 --> 00:47:45.361
♪ Crying and hoping
that soon will be our day ♪

517
00:47:45.463 --> 00:47:46.954
Paul?

518
00:47:49.567 --> 00:47:50.933
Yes?

519
00:47:51.035 --> 00:47:53.436
We need you down here.

520
00:47:53.537 --> 00:47:57.065
♪ Now that I love you ♪

521
00:47:57.174 --> 00:48:03.045
♪ Do you think
that it will end? ♪

522
00:48:05.249 --> 00:48:10.586
♪ I was above you ♪

523
00:48:10.888 --> 00:48:15.917
♪ We were just friends ♪

524
00:48:16.026 --> 00:48:19.121
♪ Now that I've found you ♪

525
00:48:19.230 --> 00:48:22.257
Daddy!

526
00:48:22.366 --> 00:48:26.201
♪ It won't take long ♪

527
00:48:31.675 --> 00:48:33.644
What's up?

528
00:48:34.945 --> 00:48:38.040
Ready when you are.

529
00:48:50.060 --> 00:48:53.622
♪ You'll lose your time when
you're racing for the light ♪

530
00:48:53.931 --> 00:48:59.928
♪ Seems like a wind-up.
we're ready to go ♪

531
00:49:00.037 --> 00:49:01.437
♪ Get ready to go ♪

532
00:49:01.539 --> 00:49:05.237
♪ Your time is coming ♪

533
00:49:05.342 --> 00:49:09.006
♪ Your time is coming ♪

534
00:49:15.219 --> 00:49:17.415
Daddy. look!

535
00:49:19.423 --> 00:49:21.949
Look. Daddy. look!

536
00:49:24.528 --> 00:49:28.090
♪ You're taking over ♪

537
00:49:28.199 --> 00:49:31.692
♪ Looking over your shoulder ♪

538
00:49:32.002 --> 00:49:34.995
♪ You're taking over ♪

539
00:49:46.684 --> 00:49:49.677
How did it go with Burns?

540
00:49:49.987 --> 00:49:53.287
He didn't buy it.

541
00:49:53.390 --> 00:49:55.291
Maybe just as well.

542
00:49:55.392 --> 00:49:57.293
There's no way
this team could cope

543
00:49:57.394 --> 00:49:59.989
with the increased
workload of linked inquiries.

544
00:50:00.097 --> 00:50:02.362
There are probably 200
statements. documents.

545
00:50:02.466 --> 00:50:05.664
officers' reports waiting
to be read and actioned.

546
00:50:05.769 --> 00:50:10.969
Recommend increasing
technical support staff.

547
00:50:12.776 --> 00:50:16.975
Failure to see that crimes
are linked... linkage blindness.

548
00:50:17.081 --> 00:50:21.018
It's the thing that will allow
the killer to strike again.

549
00:50:21.118 --> 00:50:23.678
We refuse to
recognize the series.

550
00:50:23.787 --> 00:50:26.154
and he carries on regardless.

551
00:50:29.126 --> 00:50:32.756
I didn't sell it hard
enough. Garrett.

552
00:50:33.497 --> 00:50:35.159
I'm off.

553
00:50:35.266 --> 00:50:37.497
Wait.

554
00:50:37.601 --> 00:50:39.729
How you manage to listen
to people whining all week

555
00:50:40.037 --> 00:50:40.732
in your day job

556
00:50:41.038 --> 00:50:42.062
and then volunteer

557
00:50:42.172 --> 00:50:45.040
to listen to them whining
all night on the phone.

558
00:50:45.142 --> 00:50:46.576
I'll never know.

559
00:50:46.677 --> 00:50:48.509
This from a neonatal nurse?

560
00:50:48.612 --> 00:50:50.308
All those crying babies.

561
00:50:50.414 --> 00:50:53.509
The babies I look after
are too small to cry.

562
00:50:53.617 --> 00:50:56.644
Crying would be great. Crying
means they're getting better.

563
00:50:56.754 --> 00:50:58.017
I'm gonna hit you.

564
00:50:58.122 --> 00:51:00.682
Maybe you should visit
me at work sometime.

565
00:51:00.791 --> 00:51:03.488
Maybe I should.

566
00:51:03.594 --> 00:51:05.358
Say good night to the kids.

567
00:51:05.462 --> 00:51:07.021
Good night. you two.

568
00:51:07.131 --> 00:51:08.690
Night. Daddy!

569
00:51:08.799 --> 00:51:10.791
I'll see you in the morning.

570
00:51:28.419 --> 00:51:32.049
Mummy. I need you!

571
00:52:08.592 --> 00:52:10.527
Yeah. See? I told you.

572
00:52:10.628 --> 00:52:11.857
Mary.

573
00:52:13.631 --> 00:52:14.671
I wonder if I can book you

574
00:52:14.698 --> 00:52:16.538
to look at the Exhibits
store tomorrow morning.

575
00:52:16.634 --> 00:52:18.694
Yes. ma'am.

576
00:52:18.802 --> 00:52:22.330
And I'm going to need
a lift back to the hotel.

577
00:52:22.439 --> 00:52:23.634
We're free. ma'am.

578
00:52:23.741 --> 00:52:25.107
Good.

579
00:52:25.209 --> 00:52:26.541
Finish your food.

580
00:52:26.644 --> 00:52:28.545
I'll wait in reception.

581
00:52:30.781 --> 00:52:32.306
Is it Glen?

582
00:52:34.351 --> 00:52:35.580
Yes. ma'am.

583
00:52:35.686 --> 00:52:38.781
DCI McElroy is doing
a violent crime analysis

584
00:52:38.889 --> 00:52:40.517
of the last five years.

585
00:52:40.624 --> 00:52:43.526
Could you ask him to
also include break-ins

586
00:52:43.627 --> 00:52:45.425
where valuables were ignored

587
00:52:45.529 --> 00:52:46.861
but items of clothing.

588
00:52:47.164 --> 00:52:49.656
underwear. clean or
soiled. were taken?

589
00:52:49.767 --> 00:52:50.826
Underwear. yes. ma'am.

590
00:54:24.261 --> 00:54:24.887
Who's that?

591
00:54:24.995 --> 00:54:28.261
James Olson. Detective Sergeant.

592
00:54:31.535 --> 00:54:33.697
Introduce us.

593
00:54:47.684 --> 00:54:49.880
What's going on. Sergeant?

594
00:54:49.987 --> 00:54:52.650
There's been a shooting in
a house about a mile away.

595
00:54:52.756 --> 00:54:54.725
A car was stopped
just up along there.

596
00:54:54.825 --> 00:54:56.726
We found guns and
arrested three men.

597
00:54:56.827 --> 00:54:58.261
Just waiting on the dogs.

598
00:54:58.362 --> 00:54:59.362
Explosives?

599
00:54:59.463 --> 00:55:01.830
This is Detective
Superintendent Gibson.

600
00:55:01.932 --> 00:55:04.333
She's here to review
the Monroe investigation.

601
00:55:04.434 --> 00:55:05.434
Oh. right.

602
00:55:05.536 --> 00:55:07.004
DS Olson. Nice to meet you.

603
00:55:07.304 --> 00:55:07.896
It's drugs.

604
00:55:08.005 --> 00:55:09.769
The deceased was
well-known to us.

605
00:55:11.642 --> 00:55:12.701
Will the review take long?

606
00:55:12.810 --> 00:55:15.644
A week. maybe more.

607
00:55:15.746 --> 00:55:17.044
I'm staying at the Hilton.

608
00:55:17.347 --> 00:55:18.474
Very nice.

609
00:55:18.582 --> 00:55:21.347
Room 203.

610
00:55:22.052 --> 00:55:23.782
James!

611
00:55:23.887 --> 00:55:26.356
Oi!

612
00:55:26.456 --> 00:55:29.358
Good luck with your arrests.

613
00:55:47.811 --> 00:55:50.337
I think we might have fucked up.

614
00:55:50.447 --> 00:55:52.348
What?

615
00:55:52.449 --> 00:55:53.849
- How?
- Did you not hear her?

616
00:55:53.951 --> 00:55:55.715
What?

617
00:55:55.819 --> 00:55:58.311
Robberies where items
of underwear were taken.

618
00:55:59.857 --> 00:56:01.792
Sarah Kay.

619
00:56:01.892 --> 00:56:04.020
We should have
moved her out of there.

620
00:56:04.127 --> 00:56:06.323
Put her in a hotel.
Called in CSIs.

621
00:56:06.430 --> 00:56:07.907
Jesus. the woman
more or less told us to go.

622
00:56:07.931 --> 00:56:10.799
I think we should take a look.

623
00:56:30.854 --> 00:56:34.518
Detective Superintendent
Stella Gibson?

624
00:56:34.625 --> 00:56:35.957
Ned Callan. <i>Belfast Chronicle.</i>

625
00:56:36.059 --> 00:56:36.958
Can I have a word?

626
00:56:37.060 --> 00:56:40.030
Not at the moment. no.

627
00:56:40.130 --> 00:56:41.758
Not even off the record?

628
00:56:41.865 --> 00:56:44.494
There's no such
thing. as you well know.

629
00:56:49.806 --> 00:56:52.435
Did I invite you to sit down?

630
00:56:52.542 --> 00:56:53.908
I don't think so.

631
00:56:54.011 --> 00:56:55.775
So. call the police.

632
00:56:55.879 --> 00:56:57.677
How did you find me here?

633
00:56:57.781 --> 00:56:59.477
It's a small city. Stella.

634
00:56:59.583 --> 00:57:00.881
It's not easy to hide.

635
00:57:00.984 --> 00:57:03.681
Unless. of course. you're
the murderer of Alice Monroe.

636
00:57:03.787 --> 00:57:05.722
Oh. God.

637
00:57:05.822 --> 00:57:08.724
You really are a
journalist. aren't you?

638
00:57:10.460 --> 00:57:13.396
So. why bring someone
in from the outside?

639
00:57:13.497 --> 00:57:16.160
That looks remarkably
like a vote of no confidence

640
00:57:16.466 --> 00:57:18.458
in the PSNI and
its ability to run

641
00:57:18.568 --> 00:57:21.629
an internal murder investigation
review. don't you think?

642
00:57:21.738 --> 00:57:23.070
What have you found so far?

643
00:57:23.173 --> 00:57:25.142
Staggering levels
of incompetence?

644
00:57:25.442 --> 00:57:28.708
Mr. Callan. no one
knows better than me

645
00:57:28.812 --> 00:57:33.011
how important the media is
as an investigative resource.

646
00:57:33.116 --> 00:57:38.987
but. really and truly.
you should fuck off. now.

647
00:57:40.023 --> 00:57:42.720
You have my card.

648
00:57:45.595 --> 00:57:47.427
Thank you.

649
00:57:47.531 --> 00:57:50.091
Enjoy.

650
00:59:09.546 --> 00:59:11.742
Nothing.

651
00:59:24.594 --> 00:59:27.086
This is a message for Sarah Kay.

652
00:59:27.197 --> 00:59:28.665
Sarah. this is PC
Danni Ferrington.

653
00:59:28.765 --> 00:59:30.700
I'm calling from
outside your house.

654
00:59:30.801 --> 00:59:33.134
If you are there. it is
the police at the door.

655
00:59:33.236 --> 00:59:34.795
I was hoping to speak with you

656
00:59:34.905 --> 00:59:37.636
to follow up on the incident
that occurred on Friday.

657
00:59:37.741 --> 00:59:40.643
Please ring the number I gave
you when you get this message.

658
00:59:56.026 --> 00:59:59.827
Perhaps she did go
stay with her sister.

659
